<tbody>
<tr><td><strong>Free</strong></td><td>$0</td><td>1 minute of video generation, limited avatar selection, watermark on exports</td></tr>
<tr><td><strong>Creator</strong></td><td>$24/mo</td><td>15 minutes of video generation, full avatar library, 1 personal avatar, voice cloning, no watermark, commercial usage rights</td></tr>
<tr><td><strong>Business</strong></td><td>$72/mo</td><td>30 minutes of video generation, 3 personal avatars, 3 instant voice clones, custom brand kit, team collaboration (3 seats), priority support</td></tr>
</tbody>
</table>

<p>The Creator plan at $24/month is the sweet spot for most individual creators and small teams. The 15 minutes of monthly generation is generous for regular content production — think one 3-minute video per workday, or a mix of short social clips and longer training pieces. Voice cloning, personal avatar creation, and watermark-free exports with commercial rights make this a self-contained production tool.</p>

<p>The Free tier is genuinely limited — 1 minute total, not per month — making it more of a one-time demo than a usable free plan. This is a significant gap compared to competitors who offer more generous free tiers for experimentation. If you're evaluating HeyGen, plan to use your free minute strategically to test the workflow before committing to a paid plan.</p>

<p>For teams and high-volume producers, the Business plan scales to 30 minutes/month with collaboration features and instant voice clones. However, the per-minute pricing model means costs add up quickly for heavy usage. A company producing 2 hours of video content per month would need 4 Business seats ($288/month), which may be expensive compared to traditional production alternatives for very high volumes.</p>

<h2>Pros and Cons</h2>

<h3>What We Loved ✅</h3>
<ul>
  <li><strong>Industry-leading lip-sync accuracy</strong> — Multilingual dubbing adjusts mouth movements perfectly across 40+ languages, making global content production seamless</li>
  <li><strong>Professional-quality avatars</strong> — Realistic rendering with natural expressions, gestures, and movements in most shot compositions</li>
  <li><strong>Huge time savings</strong> — Script-to-video in minutes rather than days for traditional studio production</li>
  <li><strong>Excellent voice cloning</strong> — Captures natural intonation, emotion, and personality from source recordings</li>
  <li><strong>Diverse avatar marketplace</strong> — Wide range of presenters across ages, ethnicities, and professional styles</li>
  <li><strong>Intuitive interface</strong> — Clean, well-organized editor that's easy to learn for new users</li>
</ul>

<h3>What Could Be Better ❌</h3>
<ul>
  <li><strong>Very limited free tier</strong> — Only 1 minute total, not enough for meaningful evaluation</li>
  <li><strong>Avatars slightly uncanny in close-up</strong> — Micro-expressions don't always track perfectly in extreme close-up shots</li>
  <li><strong>Voice cloning is source-dependent</strong> — Quality degrades significantly with poor source audio recordings</li>
  <li><strong>Expensive for high-volume production</strong> — Per-minute pricing model becomes costly when producing hours of content monthly</li>
  <li><strong>No native video editing</strong> — Must use external tools for complex edits, transitions, or multi-scene compositions</li>
  <li><strong>Limited custom branding on lower tiers</strong> — Full brand kit and custom backgrounds only available on Business plan</li>
</ul>

<h2>HeyGen vs Competitors</h2>

